Problem in selenium 1 and 2:
============================
let take example we are using chrome broswer version 97 for running automation
script

we are mainting the .exe version of the 97 in our local

lets suppose after 10 days google chrome has updated the broswer version to 98 

when we are trying to run now automation scripts will fail why because
your broswer version is 98 and chromedriver.exe binary version is 97 which is not compatable

then we need to do we need to download the 98 version of the .exe file and update in your project

....so on same process need to repeat when ever there is change in the broswer version 
same is applicable for the firefox and edgebroswers as well 

for Safaribroswer .exe file is not created by the Apple becuase safari broswer version will not change 
very frequently. it will change in once in 6 months 

Again the safaribroswer.exe will created by the seleniumTeam only not from the apple team

Till selenium 1 and selenium 2 creation of the binary file(.exe) have to taken care by the selenium
there is 2-3 days delay in creation of the .exe file for respective broswer version when ever there is
new broswer version released

In order avoid this delay SeleniumTeam has requested the respective vendors to take of the .exe files
release them along the new broswer version(from Selenium 3 on words)

===================================================
From Selenium 3 on words selenium has given task of creating the .exe file for the respective vendor

chromdriver.exe for google
gechokedriver.exe for the firefox team
edgedriver.exe for the microsoft edge team  

is the problem solved still yes or no

No right we have a manual step of downloading the .exe file and update in the project
Note:Selenium 1,selenium 2 and Selenium 3 used the JSON wire protocal internally communcation from the 
client code(testcases) to actual broswers
==============================================================
In order to avoid this manual step from the Selenium 4.6 onwords introduced SeleniumManager 

How SeleniumManager is working internally:
=========================================
Now vendors are updating the respective binary files(.exe) under the Dashboard 
called CFT(Chrome for Testing)
here is the link for the same
https://googlechromelabs.github.io/chrome-for-testing/

SeleniumManager will download the respective .exe based on the OperatingSystem and 
broswer of the local system and place it in the C:\Users\Shankar<respectiveusername>\.cache
under .cache folder 
Note: .cache folder is already present 

under this .cache folder seleniumManager will create the folder called "selenium" and place the 
respective .exe files under this

Note: SeleniumManager has backword compatibility as well 

